<chapter id="mux">

	<title>MUX
	</title>
	<para>
		The
		<literal>Multiplexer</literal>
		(
		<acronym>MUX</acronym>
		) is designed as stack wrapper. Serves two purposes:
	</para>
	<variablelist>
		<varlistentry>
			<term>expose stack</term>
			<listitem>
				<para>
					It exposes stack and allows to share it between multiple
					listeners.
					Stack follows life cycle of
					<acronym>MUX</acronym>
					- it is created and destroyed with
					<acronym>MUX</acronym>.
				</para>
			</listitem>
		</varlistentry>
		<varlistentry>
			<term>expose management operations</term>
			<listitem>
				<para>
					It exposes management operation for
					<acronym>JOPR</acronym>
					console. For specifc information please refer to management console
					guide.
				</para>
			</listitem>
		</varlistentry>
	</variablelist>

